14/04/23/micropasts-latest-tech-update","author":["Daniel Pett"],"featuredImage":null}}},{"node":{"excerpt":"Since late 2013, the MicroPasts team has been preparing the British Museum‘s (BM) Bronze Age Index to be the first offering on our crowd-sourcing platform. This corpus consists of around 30,000 (roughly A4 sized) cards (holding information going back to as early as 1913). The majority of these are double sided and generally have text on the front and a line drawing on the reverse (there are many…","frontmatter":{"title":"Preparing the British Museum Bronze Age index for transcription","permalink":"/2014/04/30/preparing-the-index","author":["Jennifer Wexler"],"featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/7a2665ca4f279a42114000dce193e19a/20850/MicroPasts-%C2%B7-Application-British-Museum-Bronze-Age-Index-Drawer-B16-%C2%B7-Contribute.png","srcSet":"/static/7a2665ca4f279a42114000dce193e19a/994f0/MicroPasts-%C2%B7-Application-British-Museum-Bronze-Age-Index-Drawer-B16-%C2%B7-Contribute.png 100w,\n/static/7a2665ca4f279a42114000dce193e19a/4bbad/MicroPasts-%C2%B7-Application-British-Museum-Bronze-Age-Index-Drawer-B16-%C2%B7-Contribute.png 200w,\n/static/7a2665ca4f279a42114000dce193e19a/20850/MicroPasts-%C2%B7-Application-British-Museum-Bronze-Age-Index-Drawer-B16-%C2%B7-Contribute.png 400w,\n/static/7a2665ca4f279a42114000dce193e19a/ddb6f/MicroPasts-%C2%B7-Application-British-Museum-Bronze-Age-Index-Drawer-B16-%C2%B7-Contribute.png 800w","sizes":"(min-width: 400px) 400px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/7a2665ca4f279a42114000dce193e19a/90ebf/MicroPasts-%C2%B7-Application-British-Museum-Bronze-Age-Index-Drawer-B16-%C2%B7-Contribute.webp 100w,\n/static/7a2665ca4f279a42114000dce193e19a/59b5d/MicroPasts-%C2%B7-Application-British-Museum-Bronze-Age-Index-Drawer-B16-%C2%B7-Contribute.webp 200w,\n/static/7a2665ca4f279a42114000dce193e19a/697e6/MicroPasts-%C2%B7-Application-British-Museum-Bronze-Age-Index-Drawer-B16-%C2%B7-Contribute.webp 400w,\n/static/7a2665ca4f279a42114000dce193e19a/96b3c/MicroPasts-%C2%B7-Application-British-Museum-Bronze-Age-Index-Drawer-B16-%C2%B7-Contribute.webp 800w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 400px) 400px, 100vw"}]},"width":400,"height":250}}}}}},{"node":{"excerpt":"We are in the process of adding a new photo-masking application to the MicroPasts site. This is going to be a bit of a ‘pop-up shop’ as it will only include one Bronze Age British hoard, although it is one of considerable importance. A hoard is an archaeological terms for two or more objects, normally of metal, deposited together. In some cases these were buried with the intention of recovery, but…","frontmatter":{"title":"3D Modelling of the Arreton Down Hoard","permalink":"/2014/05/30/3d-modelling-of-the-arreton-down-hoard","author":["Adi Keinan-Schoonbaert"],"featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/4c290a5fcd5a0c050f97c16096b32466/d6c95/3D-Scanning-Franks-2.jpg","srcSet":"/static/4c290a5fcd5a0c050f97c16096b32466/c9998/3D-Scanning-Franks-2.jpg 100w,\n/static/4c290a5fcd5a0c050f97c16096b32466/503f5/3D-Scanning-Franks-2.jpg 200w,\n/static/4c290a5fcd5a0c050f97c16096b32466/d6c95/3D-Scanning-Franks-2.jpg 400w,\n/static/4c290a5fcd5a0c050f97c16096b32466/5af6b/3D-Scanning-Franks-2.jpg 800w","sizes":"(min-width: 400px) 400px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/4c290a5fcd5a0c050f97c16096b32466/90ebf/3D-Scanning-Franks-2.webp 100w,\n/static/4c290a5fcd5a0c050f97c16096b32466/59b5d/3D-Scanning-Franks-2.webp 200w,\n/static/4c290a5fcd5a0c050f97c16096b32466/697e6/3D-Scanning-Franks-2.webp 400w,\n/static/4c290a5fcd5a0c050f97c16096b32466/96b3c/3D-Scanning-Franks-2.webp 800w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 400px) 400px, 100vw"}]},"width":400,"height":250}}}}}}]}},"pageContext":{"tag":"Crowdsou